WEBVTT

00:00:00.504 --> 00:00:02.192
Your spine is made up of a

00:00:02.190 --> 00:00:03.968
column of bones with a space

00:00:03.960 --> 00:00:05.896
in the center for the spinal cord

00:00:05.890 --> 00:00:07.760
called the spinal canal.

00:00:07.904 --> 00:00:09.952
Disks between the vertebra act

00:00:09.950 --> 00:00:12.416
as shock absorbers when you move your back.

00:00:12.410 --> 00:00:13.920
A ruptured disk,

00:00:13.920 --> 00:00:15.336
also called a herniated

00:00:15.330 --> 00:00:16.568
or bulging disk,

00:00:16.560 --> 00:00:18.584
or a narrowed spinal canal,

00:00:18.580 --> 00:00:20.544
termed spinal stenosis,

00:00:20.540 --> 00:00:22.120
can put pressure on or

00:00:22.120 --> 00:00:24.192
irritate the sciatic nerve.

00:00:24.584 --> 00:00:27.552
This nerve, actually a group of nerves,

00:00:27.550 --> 00:00:29.400
runs from the lower spine,

00:00:29.400 --> 00:00:31.544
down the leg to the foot.

00:00:31.808 --> 00:00:33.744
Irritation of the sciatic nerve

00:00:33.740 --> 00:00:35.352
is known as sciatica

00:00:35.350 --> 00:00:36.816
and can cause pain,

00:00:36.810 --> 00:00:39.336
numbness, or tingling in the leg.

